Vendored ExprTk expression evaluator
=====================================

RuleMonkey's rate-law / function / parameter expression evaluator is
bngsim::ExprTkEvaluator (see issue #6).  These three files are copied
verbatim from BNGsim and are compiled ONLY in a standalone RuleMonkey
build: CMakeLists.txt gates them on `if(TARGET bngsim::expression)`, so
inside a BNGsim build RM links the host's copy instead.

Source repo  : BNGsim (github.com/wshlavacek/PyBNF-Private, bngsim/ subdir)
Pinned commit: f5cbc33c42f9c84ade79287cb80da44c908e1406

Vendored files (copied verbatim, no edits):
  third_party/exprtk/exprtk.hpp                         <- bngsim third_party/exprtk/exprtk.hpp
  third_party/bngsim_expr/include/bngsim/expression.hpp <- bngsim include/bngsim/expression.hpp
  third_party/bngsim_expr/src/expression.cpp            <- bngsim src/expression.cpp

Refresh / drift-check
---------------------
This file is maintained by scripts/vendor_exprtk.py — the `Pinned commit:`
line above is the machine-readable pin (do not reformat it).

  scripts/vendor_exprtk.py            # re-copy the 3 files from BNGsim main, re-pin
  scripts/vendor_exprtk.py --ref <r>  # ... from a specific BNGsim ref/tag/commit
  scripts/vendor_exprtk.py --check    # verify the 3 files still match the pin

exprtk.hpp is header-only — two identical copies merge fine, but version
skew between RM's copy and BNGsim's is undefined behavior (an ODR
violation).  `--check` is the guard against that drift; run it (or wire it
into CI) when bumping the pin.  See dev/exprtk_swap_plan_2026_05_16.md §4.3a.
